2001-04-22  Rich Gade  <rgade@users.sourceforge.net>

	* /cvsroot/ggz/gtk-client/ggz-gtk-client.spec, /cvsroot/ggz/gtk-client/ggz-gtk.spec:
	- Updated RPM spec file to new distro name

2001-04-20  bmh  <bmh@users.sourceforge.net>

	* /cvsroot/ggz/ggz/src/frontend/gtk/glade/main.glade, /cvsroot/ggz/ggz/src/frontend/gtk/client.c, /cvsroot/ggz/ggz/src/frontend/gtk/game.c, /cvsroot/ggz/ggz/src/frontend/gtk/ggz.c, /cvsroot/ggz/ggz/src/frontend/gtk/login.c:
	- Pulled most sensitivity stuff into a state callback
	  ggz_state_sensitivity()
	- Rethink what needs to be sensitive when
	- This should fix Rich's Lag bug #4

	* /cvsroot/ggz/ggz/src/frontend/gtk/game.c:
	- When the game is over, check the state of the server, and only call
	  ggzcore_room_leave_table() if we're actually *at* the table,
	  otherwise install game_delayed_leave() as a callback to the
	  GGZ_STATE_CHANGE event.
	- New function game_delayed_leave() will call
	  ggzcore_room_leave_table() once we finally reach the "at table"
	  state.
	- All of this fixes Rich's lag bug #2

2001-04-14  bmh  <bmh@users.sourceforge.net>

	* /cvsroot/ggz/ggz/src/frontend/gtk/client.c, /cvsroot/ggz/ggz/src/frontend/gtk/game.c, /cvsroot/ggz/ggz/src/frontend/gtk/launch.c:
	- Check return values of ggzcore_room_{join|launch}_table() before
	  proceeding.  If errors, post a dialog.
	- Check server state before initializing game module.  Yeah, it'll
	  error out later if the state is wrong, but this provides a simple
	  check earlier on in the process.

2001-04-10  bmh  <bmh@users.sourceforge.net>

	* /cvsroot/ggz/ggz/src/frontend/gtk/client.c, /cvsroot/ggz/ggz/src/frontend/gtk/game.c, /cvsroot/ggz/ggz/src/frontend/gtk/game.h, /cvsroot/ggz/ggz/src/frontend/gtk/ggz.c, /cvsroot/ggz/ggz/src/frontend/gtk/glade/launch.glade, /cvsroot/ggz/ggz/src/frontend/gtk/launch.c:
	- Do a bunch of error checking in game_init() to see if we're in a
	  room, or already at a table, and if the module actually exists, etc.
	- Actually create the object in game_init()
	- Call game_init() from launch_create_or_raise() so that we don't
	  popup launch dialog if the game does not initialize properly
	- New function game_launch() to do the actual launching
	- Call game_launch() if the "Launch" button is pressed
	- Call game_destroy() if the launch "Cancel" button is pressed
	- Call game_destroy() from game_launch() if the launch fails

2001-04-09  bmh  <bmh@users.sourceforge.net>

	* /cvsroot/ggz/ggz/src/frontend/gtk/client.c:
	- Removed unnecessary debugging statements

2001-04-07  bmh  <bmh@users.sourceforge.net>

	* /cvsroot/ggz/ggz/src/frontend/gtk/client.c:
	- Pulled table joining code into function client_join_table()
	- Reordered error checking so we don't get errors every time we join a
	  table

	* /cvsroot/ggz/ggz/src/frontend/gtk/client.c, /cvsroot/ggz/ggz/src/frontend/gtk/glade/main.glade:
	- Cleaned up client_room_clist_event code a bit (in an effort to
	  understand it a bit better)

	* /cvsroot/ggz/ggz/src/frontend/gtk/client.c:
	- Check server state before attemoting to enter room:
	- If not OK, pop up appropriate error message
	- If attempt to join fails popup an error message
	- If singleclick room entering is enabled, desensitize the room list
	  while between rooms to prevent trying to join two rooms at once.
	  A bug (perhaps in GTK?) causes the mouse pointer to get "stuck" if
	  we do this with doubleclick room entering

	* /cvsroot/ggz/ggz/src/frontend/gtk/ggz.c:
	- Handle room join failures: popup a message explanation

