2001-03-03  bmh  <bmh@users.sourceforge.net>

	* /cvsroot/ggz/ggz/src/frontend/gtk/ggz.c, /cvsroot/ggz/ggz/src/frontend/gtk/main.c:
	- Disabled MEMDETAIL debugging by default
	- Split out code to display table and player lists into functions
	  display_tables() and display_players() : these should probably go in
	  client.c
	- Call display_tables() upon table list and table updates
	- Call display_players() upon player list, playuer enter and leave,
	  and player updates.  This keeps us from requesting the data from the
	  server again
	- New functions for handling GGZ_NET_ERROR and GGZ_PROTOCOL_ERROR:
	  right now they just print a line to stdout.  They should pop up a
	  dialog

